      <div class="govspeak">
<div class="call-to-action">
<h2 id="stay-up-to-date">Stay up to date</h2>

<p>A Brexit deal has been agreed but needs to be ratified. The UK could still leave with no deal on 31 October 2019 if the UK and EU do not approve and sign the withdrawal agreement.</p>

<p>This page tells you how to prepare for Brexit and will be updated if anything changes. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/email-signup/?topic=/brexit">Sign up for email alerts</a> to get the latest information.</p>
</div>

<p>The government has guaranteed that UK organisations will continue to receive funding if they successfully bid into EU funded programmes before the end of 2020.</p>

<p>Register if you receive or have applied for funding from:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Civil Protection Mechanism</li>
  <li>Competitiveness of Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises (COSME)</li>
  <li>Connecting Europe Facility (CEF) telecoms</li>
  <li>Creative Europe</li>
  <li>Employment and Social Innovation (EaSI)</li>
  <li>Erasmus+</li>
  <li>Europe for Citizens</li>
  <li>European Solidarity Corps</li>
  <li>Health for Growth</li>
  <li>Rights, Equality, and Citizenship Programme (RECP)</li>
</ul>

<div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
<p>There’s a different way to register if you receive <a rel="external" href="https://apply-for-innovation-funding.service.gov.uk/eu-grant/overview">Horizon 2020 funding</a>.</p>
</div>

<p>After you register, the government department responsible for your programme will contact you.</p>

<p>Do not register if:</p>

<ul>
  <li>you receive or have applied for funding from a different EU programme - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/european-and-domestic-funding-after-brexit">check what to do for different programmes</a>
</li>
  <li>you’re already in contact with a government department about what will happen to your funding after Brexit</li>
  <li>your project will have finished before Brexit but the final payment will come after Brexit - contact <a href="mailto:helpdesk.grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk">helpdesk.grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk</a> if you’re told that you will not receive the final payment</li>
</ul>

<div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
<p>Read more about the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/the-governments-guarantee-for-eu-funded-programmes-if-theres-no-brexit-deal">government’s guarantee</a> for EU funded programmes.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="how-to-register">How to register</h2>

<p>You’ll need your Companies House or Charity Commission number, as well as details from your grant agreement if you have one.</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Download and fill in the <span id="attachment_3753025" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/841500/EU_direct_bid_funding_registration_form.ods">EU direct bid funding registration form</a>
  (<span class="type"><abbr title="OpenDocument Spreadsheet">ODS</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">16.8KB</span>)
</span></p>
  </li>
  <li>Create an email with the programme name as the subject.</li>
  <li>Attach the registration form and your full grant agreements, including any annexes. If the email would be larger than 25MB, split it into multiple emails each with the same subject line.</li>
  <li>You do not need to write anything in the body of the email. Send it to <a href="mailto:grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk">grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk</a>
</li>
</ol>

<p>You should receive an automatic reply shortly after you send the email.</p>

<p>Your details will then be passed to the government department responsible for the programme. They’ll contact you within 15 working days.</p>

<h2 id="get-help">Get help</h2>

<p>Email <a href="mailto:helpdesk.grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk">helpdesk.grants.registration@cabinetoffice.gov.uk</a> if you:</p>

<ul>
  <li>have a question or need help to register</li>
  <li>need to change the details you submitted - do not try to register again</li>
  <li>want to give feedback on the registration process</li>
</ul>

<p>You’ll usually get a reply within 5 working days.</p>

<h2 id="privacy">Privacy</h2>

<p>Read the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/privacy-notice-for-grants-management-function-recipient-registration">privacy notice</a> for registration.</p>
</div>
</div>


